2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0398
HOUSE BILL NO. HB0244
Carbon dioxide pipelines-eminent domain prohibition.
Sponsored by: Representative(s) Winter, Allemand, Angelos,
Strock and Wharff
A BILL
for
1 AN ACT relating to eminent domain; prohibiting persons from
2 using the power of eminent domain to place pipelines
3 conveying carbon dioxide for the purposes of carbon
4 capture, utilization or storage; specifying applicability;
5 making conforming amendments; and providing for an
6 effective date.
7
8 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Wyoming:
9
10 Section 1. W.S. 1-26-814 and 1-26-815(a) are amended
11 to read:
12
13 1-26-814. Right of eminent domain granted;
14 exceptions; petroleum or other pipeline companies;
15 purposes.
1 HB0244

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0398
1
2 (a) Whenever any utility or any petroleum or other
3 pipeline company, authorized to do business in this state,
4 has not acquired by gift or purchase any land, real estate
5 or claim required for the construction, maintenance and
6 operation of their facilities and appurtenances or which
7 may be affected by any operation connected with the
8 construction or maintenance of the same, the utility or
9 company has the right of eminent domain and may condemn the
10 easement required by the utility or company, except as
11 provided by subsection (b) of this section.
12
13 (b) No person shall use the power of eminent domain
14 to place pipelines for the purpose of conveying or storing
15 carbon dioxide for the purpose of carbon capture,
16 utilization or storage in order to meet the low-carbon
17 energy standards specified under W.S. 37-18-101 and
18 37-18-102.
19
20 1-26-815. Right of eminent domain granted; ways of
21 necessity for authorized businesses; purposes; extent.
22
