1 (a) Except as provided by W.S. 1-26-814(b), any
2 person, association, company or corporation authorized to
3 do business in this state may appropriate by condemnation a
4 way of necessity over, across or on so much of the lands or
5 real property of others as necessary for the location,
6 construction, maintenance and use of reservoirs, drains,
7 flumes, ditches including return flow and wastewater
8 ditches, underground water pipelines, pumping stations and
9 other necessary appurtenances, canals, electric power
10 transmission lines and distribution systems, railroad
11 trackage, sidings, spur tracks, tramways, roads or mine
12 truck haul roads required in the course of their business
13 for agricultural, mining, exploration drilling and
14 production of oil and gas, milling, electric power
15 transmission and distribution, domestic, municipal or
16 sanitary purposes, or for the transportation of coal from
17 any coal mine or railroad line or for the transportation of
18 oil and gas from any well.
19
20 Section 2. This act shall apply to carbon capture,
21 utilization and storage projects for which construction
22 commences on or after July 1, 2025.
